text:
Sarawak Immigration Dept. detains seven Indian nationals with fake passports  
Seven men of Indian nationals have been detained and nine fake foreign passports and approval documents for Temporary Working Visit Pass seized by the Sarawak Immigration Department in a raid on a house in Jalan Bampflyde, Kuching Wednesday.
The raid was carried out following a public tip-off at 5.25 pm and three weeks of intelligence operation, informed its director, Mohamad Zulfikar Ahmad.
Mohamad Zulfikar said all of the suspects, who do not possess valid passport or travel documents, were detained for further investigation.
At a press conference in Kuching he said, “Another man at large, believed to be the mastermind, is being hunted to facilitate further investigation into the case.
 
“We have distributed his photofit to the authorities at all entry points in the state as we believe he is still in Sarawak,”
Other items seized were two printers, three laptop computers and a computer monitor.
